nodes.bodyText: @genryxy I see that this command is executed twice, is it really necessary?

@olenagerasimova thanks. I try to verify that artifacts are cached. Maybe, it would be nice just to check that storage contains the key, but I have some troubles with it therefore implemented so. I'll try to check through storage and execute this command only once.

@genryxy have you tried simply check temp directory structure? You can add brake point, copy path and use ls -la. As far as see files should be ./subdir/repos/. When you understand where files are, you can create FileStorage instance over subdir and check that files are loaded by corresponding keys
@olenagerasimova yes, I tried to check temp directory. It has artipie.yaml, settings, repos/my-maven.yaml, repos/_credentials.yml
